  "texts": [
    "The approach involves connecting words with dependency relationships based on dependency path information in the embedding space.",
    "This method effectively distinguishes words with similar contexts but different syntactic functions.",
    "RNCRF (Recursive Neural Network with Conditional Random Fields) (Wang et al. 2016a) is a recursive neural network based on sentence-level dependency trees.",
    "Its purpose is to learn high-level feature representations for each word in a sentence within the context and to understand the association between aspect and opinion terms based on the dependency structure.",
    "The most significant advantage of RNCRF lies in its ability to capture the underlying dual propagation between aspect and opinion terms."
  ],
